    <h2>1. Undercounter Refrigerators: Space-Saving Cold Storage</h2>
    <p>Undercounter refrigerators are compact units that fit beneath a worktop, typically 85 cm tall to match standard counter height. They're ideal for small bakeries, cafés, and cloud kitchens where floor space is at a premium. An undercounter fridge under the prep table keeps ingredients like butter, eggs, cream cheese, and fillings within arm's reach while baking.</p>
    <p>Capacity typically ranges from 100 to 200 litres. Most commercial undercounter units are built with stainless steel exteriors for easy cleaning and durability in commercial kitchen environments. They run on standard single-phase power, making installation straightforward.</p>

    <h3>Undercounter Refrigerator Prices in India 2026</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>100–120 L, Indian brand (Voltas, Blue Star, Rockwell)</strong>: ₹18,000 – ₹28,000</li>
      <li><strong>150–175 L, commercial grade</strong>: ₹28,000 – ₹40,000</li>
      <li><strong>200 L, imported brand (Foster, True, Gram)</strong>: ₹40,000 – ₹60,000</li>
      <li><strong>Drawer-type undercounter (2–3 drawers)</strong>: ₹55,000 – ₹95,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For a small home bakery or cloud kitchen, a domestic undercounter refrigerator (₹15,000–25,000) can serve as a starting point, but commercial-grade units are more durable and are built for continuous operation in hot kitchen environments.</p>

    <h3>Key Features to Look for in Undercounter Fridges</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Temperature range:</strong> Commercial undercounters should hold 0°C–8°C reliably, even when frequently opened</li>
      <li><strong>Door seal quality:</strong> In India's humidity, poor seals lead to ice buildup and compressor overwork</li>
      <li><strong>Self-closing door:</strong> Essential in a busy kitchen where doors are constantly opened</li>
      <li><strong>Ventilation direction:</strong> Front-ventilated models can be built into cabinetry; rear-vent models cannot</li>
      <li><strong>Auto-defrost:</strong> Saves maintenance time; manual defrost units require weekly attention in Indian climate</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Upright Reach-In Refrigerators: The Workhorse of Bakery Cold Storage</h2>
    <p>Upright reach-in refrigerators are the most common commercial refrigerators in Indian bakeries. Single-door models (200–400 L) are sufficient for small to medium bakeries. Double-door models (400–800 L) are better for operations that need to store significant quantities of perishable ingredients — bulk butter, cream, eggs, fresh fruit fillings, and chilled dough.</p>
    <p>In India's climate, a commercial reach-in refrigerator works much harder than its domestic counterpart. Ambient temperatures of 35–45°C in summer mean the compressor runs almost continuously. This is why commercial-grade compressors — designed for tropical climates — are essential. Domestic refrigerators used in bakery kitchens typically fail within 1–2 years due to the continuous load.</p>

    <h3>Reach-In Refrigerator Prices in India 2026</h3>
