      <li><strong>200–250 L single door, Indian brand</strong>: ₹28,000 – ₹42,000</li>
      <li><strong>300–400 L single door, Indian brand</strong>: ₹40,000 – ₹65,000</li>
      <li><strong>400 L single door, imported brand</strong>: ₹60,000 – ₹95,000</li>
      <li><strong>400–500 L double door, Indian brand</strong>: ₹55,000 – ₹90,000</li>
      <li><strong>600–800 L double door, Indian brand</strong>: ₹80,000 – ₹1,30,000</li>
      <li><strong>600–800 L double door, imported brand</strong>: ₹1,20,000 – ₹1,80,000</li>
      <li><strong>Triple-door (1000–1200 L)</strong>: ₹1,40,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Top Commercial Refrigerator Brands in India</h3>
    <p><strong>Indian Brands:</strong> Voltas (Tata), Blue Star, Rockwell, Sterling, Elanpro, and Maxx Cold are popular Indian commercial refrigerator brands. They're widely serviced across India, which is a major advantage. Voltas and Blue Star are the most trusted for after-sales support.</p>
    <p><strong>Imported Brands:</strong> True (USA), Foster (UK), Gram (Denmark), Liebherr (Germany), and Electrolux Professional are the premium options. They typically cost 50–100% more than Indian equivalents but offer better build quality, more precise temperature control, and higher energy efficiency ratings.</p>
    <p><strong>Best value for most Indian bakeries:</strong> Elanpro or Rockwell for budget; Blue Star for mid-range; True or Gram if you're running a premium patisserie.</p>

