    <h2>6. Walk-In Cold Rooms: When You Need Industrial Cold Storage</h2>
    <p>Walk-in cold rooms are custom-built insulated rooms with commercial refrigeration systems. They're the most cost-effective cold storage option per litre once you exceed 800–1000 litres of storage requirement. A typical small walk-in cold room for a medium-large bakery costs ₹2.5–5 lakh installed, including the refrigeration unit, insulated panels, floor, and door.</p>
    <p>Walk-in cold rooms in India are typically built with polyurethane (PU) foam insulated panels of 60–100mm thickness. Thicker panels mean better insulation and lower running costs — important in Indian summers where ambient temperatures can be 40°C+. In northern India, 80–100mm panels are recommended; in cooler regions, 60mm may suffice.</p>

